article.headline: Fairfield 81, Manhattan 73 (2OT)
article.story: BRIDGEPORT, Conn. (AP) -- DeWitt Maxwell scored five of his 22 points in the second overtime as Fairfield beat Manhattan 81-73 in a Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference game Tuesday. Terrence Todd also scored 22 for Fairfield (3-2, 1-0 MAAC), including 19 after halftime. Fairfield lost a five-point lead in the final minute of regulation and overcame a seven-point deficit in the first overtime. Peter Mulligan scored a team-high 19 points for Manhattan (3-1, 0-1), which lost four players to fouls. Arturo Dubois added 14 points. Manhattan freshman Jeff Xavier, who forced overtime with a pair of free throws in the final second, scored nine points in the first 2:02 of overtime and Manhattan led 67-60. But Deng Gai hit a 3-pointer and Kudjo Sogadzi made two free throws and a driving layup to tie the game at 67. Todd had a chance to win it in the final seconds of the first overtime for Fairfield, but his runner in the lane rolled out. The Stags broke the game open with a 9-0 run in the second extra period. Fairfield led 54-49 after two free throws by Todd with 20 seconds left in regulation when Jason Wingate hit a 3-pointer for Manhattan. Gai hit one of two free throws to make it 55-52, but he fouled Wingate on a 3-pointer with 3 seconds left. Wingate hit two of three free throws to make it 55-54, and Gai followed with one foul shot. Xavier was then fouled at midcourt by Tyquawn Goode with 0.2 seconds on the clock and he made both free throws to force overtime.
